issue.title: fix(cli): prevents next step until an available commit type is selected
issue.body:
Hi,

Recently, I started using git-cc and I'm really enjoying it. I've found a behavior that I don't know if is intended.

When a invalid commit type (a commit type that is not listed in the option list) is selected,  user can still advances to the next screen and then to the next. But after confirming, user returns to the initial screen.

With this PR, user can only advance to the select commit scope screen when a valid commit type was selected in the previous screen.

comment.body: I'd like to alert the user about the invalid option, too, but implementing error messages (#20) isn't a blocker for this PR.

issue.title: the omnibus db doesn't contain any partitioned indices
issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
```sql
select distinct relkind from pg_catalog.pg_class order by relkind;
/* yields
 S => sequence
 c => composite type
 f => foreign table
 i => index
 m => materialized view
 p => partitioned table
 r => ordinary table
 t => TOAST table
 v => view
*/
```

**Expected behavior**
I'd expect to see at least one partitioned index
```diff
  /*
   S => sequence
   c => composite type
   f => foreign table
   i => index
+  I => partitioned index
   m => materialized view
   p => partitioned table
   r => ordinary table
   t => TOAST table
   v => view
  */
```
